-- Cotton Futures Decline From 15-Year High in New York, Halting Week's Rally
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2010-09-22T17:54:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/cotton-futures-decline-from-15-year-high-in-new-york-halting-week-s-rally.html
Cotton futures for December
delivery fell 0.43 cent, or 0.4 percent, to $1.0036 a pound at
1:53 p.m. on ICE Futures U.S. in New York. Earlier, the price
jumped 2.5 percent to $1.0334, the highest level since 1995.
Before today, prices rallied for four straight days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
